<title>UK: CONNEX S-CENTRAL DRIVERS REJECT DISPUTE DEAL.</title>
<headline>CONNEX S-CENTRAL DRIVERS REJECT DISPUTE DEAL.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-08-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>Train drivers working for the Connex South Central company which operates services between the south coast of England and London's Victoria station have rejected an offer aimed at ending an industrial dispute, the ASLEF union said on Friday.</p>
<p>It said the drivers voted almost three to one against the offer which would demand changes in working practices in return for a cut in the working week to 37 hours.</p>
<p>New talks are planned next week to end the dispute which hit services earlier this summer because of a ban on overtime and rest day working.</p>
